    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-06-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="129" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                <head>No. 4.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Earl <persName type="from">Granville</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Lowell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign
                                    Office</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-06-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 17,
                            1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                        your letter of the 10th instant, requesting to be furnished with the
                        particulars of the charge against Daniel Sweeney, or McSweeney, who is
                        stated to be a United States citizen, and who was arrested under the act for
                        the better protection of person and property in Ireland of the 2d March,
                        1881, on the 2d instant, and lodged in Dundalk jail.</p>
                <p>In reply, I beg leave to acquaint you that I have referred your application
                        to the proper department of Her Majesty’s Government.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GRANVILLE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
